<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,795,1580]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Redescription. Adult. Male (
<figureCitation box="[526,611,943,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 17" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1932,1955]" captionTargetBox="[203,1433,242,1880]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1911]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 17. Adults of Dracontogena. 10. D. bernardi Karisch. male. 11 – 12. D. solii n. sp. males. 13. D. solii n. sp. female. 14 – 16. D. kingstoni n. sp. males. 17. D. kingstoni n. sp. female. Scale 10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282271/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Fig. 
<number box="[580,611,943,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
). Head: Blackish brown. Antenna dark grey, scape white. Labial palpus 1.5 times diameter of eye, blackish brown, extreme tip white. Thorax: Brownish grey, blackish in front, white posterior scale tuft; tegulae pale brown. Legs dark grey, tarsi with paler rings, tibiae with basal, medial and distal light dots, hind tibia with grey scale tuft. Wingspan 20.0–23.0 mm. Forewing upperside black, with weak brown suffusion in terminal third; dorsal maculae pure white, connection between them not interrupted, outer one may have one or two small dark dots on dorsum. Hindwing light brownish grey; scales in cell modified, narrow, darkened; veins darkened; termen slightly concave before anal corner; fringes white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,795,1580]" box="[199,400,1195,1219]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,795,1580]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[380,523,1231,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 46" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[168,1435,469,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,469,1757]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 46. Male genitalia in Dracontogena. 41. D. bernardi Karisch. (slide L. Aarvik 2808). 42. D. bernardi Karisch, phallus (slide L. Aarvik 2808). 43. D. solii n. sp. (slide NHMO 2010). 44. D. solii n. sp. phallus (slide NHMO 2010). 45. D. tonitrualis (Meyrick). 46. D. metamorphica (Meyrick). Scale figs. 41, 43: 1 mm., figs. 42, 44: 0.5 mm. Figs. 45 – 46 from Karisch (2005)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282275/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Figs. 
<number box="[447,523,1231,1255]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" value="41.42">41, 42</number>
</figureCitation>
). Indistinguishable from those of 
<taxonomicName box="[914,999,1231,1255]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Dracontogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[914,999,1231,1255]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">D. solii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1009,1072,1232,1255]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Vesica (n= 
<number box="[1206,1219,1231,1255]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" value="3.0">3</number>
) with 
<number box="[1296,1365,1231,1255]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" value="14.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="11.0">11–17</number>
small cornuti. Tergite 
<number box="[329,343,1267,1291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[359,440,1267,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 23 – 33" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1845,1868]" captionTargetBox="[164,1432,524,1797]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,519,1823]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 23 – 33. Tergite 8 in males of Dracontogena. 23. D. continentalis Karisch (slide L. Aarvik 2735). 24. D. agassizi n. sp. (slide T. Karisch 2235). 25. D. rubondoensis n. sp. (slide L. Aarvik 2734). 26. D. bjornstadi n. sp. (slide L. Aarvik 2733). 27. D. angolensis n. sp. (slide BMNH 28995). 28. D. bernardi Karisch. (slide L. Aarvik 2808). 29. D. solii n. sp. (slide NHMO 2010). 30. D. kingstoni n sp. (slide L. Aarvik 2010.004). 31. D. gilligani n. sp. (slide BMNH 28993). 32. D. sundi n. sp. (slide L. Aarvik 2809). 33. D. deltozyga (Meyrick) (slide L. Aarvik 2007.010). Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/282273/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Fig. 
<number box="[411,440,1267,1291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) long, with oblique lateral sides, becoming broader towards posterior end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,795,1580]" box="[199,400,1303,1327]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,795,1580]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName authority="Karisch" authorityName="Karisch" box="[325,550,1339,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Dracontogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardi">
<emphasis box="[325,456,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">D. bernardi</emphasis>
Karisch
</taxonomicName>
has the same hindwing shape as 
<taxonomicName box="[922,1004,1339,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Dracontogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[922,1004,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">D. solii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1011,1071,1340,1363]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
However, it can immediately be separated from the latter by the lack of the conspicuous black scale patch on the hindwing upperside.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,795,1580]" box="[199,1404,1411,1435]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Distribution. Known from the eastern part of the 
<collectingCountry box="[748,1099,1411,1435]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">Democratic Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
and from western 
<collectingCountry box="[1309,1400,1411,1435]" name="Uganda" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">Uganda</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,795,1580]" box="[199,910,1447,1471]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Biology. The habitat in 
<collectingCountry box="[464,551,1447,1471]" name="Uganda" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">Uganda</collectingCountry>
is the edge of mountain forests.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,795,1580]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">
Remarks. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authority="Karisch" authorityName="Karisch" box="[591,830,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Dracontogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardi">
<emphasis box="[591,729,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">D. bernardi</emphasis>
Karisch
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[898,987,1483,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Dracontogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solii" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[898,987,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">D. solii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1001,1068,1484,1507]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are virtually indistinguishable, indicating that the two are closely related in spite of their striking external differences. 
<bibRefCitation author="Karisch" box="[1148,1319,1519,1543]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" refString="Karisch, T. (2005) Ubersicht uber die Gattung Dracontogena Diakonoff 1970 (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae: Olethreutinae: Grapholitini). Linzer biologische Beitrage, 37, 457 - 476." type="journal article" year="2005">
Karisch (
<number box="[1252,1311,1519,1543]" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Dracontogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">D. bernardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName box="[325,487,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Eucosma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metamorphica">
<emphasis box="[325,487,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">metamorphica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group; however, it is herewith transferred to the 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1164,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Dracontogena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="355" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niphadonta">
<emphasis box="[1036,1164,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="355">niphadonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group.
</paragraph>
